      "content": "Yellowing leaves on the bottom of tomato plants can be due to a variety of reasons, but it's often a sign of root bound conditions or a lack of nutrients. It's possible that your plant has outgrown its container and needs to be transplanted into a larger pot with fresh soil and fertilizer. You can also try adjusting the watering schedule to ensure the roots aren't getting too wet or dry. A quick check of the roots should also help determine if they're root bound.",
